    "recap_url": "https://www.emueagles.com/news/2026/3/22/baseball-secures-first-mac-series-win-under-beerman-tops-akron-behind-rutherfords-eight-strikeouts",
    "recap_headline": "Eastern Michigan Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Re-Watch Game\n|\nCal Rutherford Highlight\nYPSILANTI, Mich. (EMUEagles.com) \u2013\nThe Eastern Michigan University baseball team powered past the University of Akron, 6-2, Sunday, March 22, at Oestrike Stadium, securing its first Mid-American Conference series win in the Interim Head Coach\nTrevor Beerman\nera (2026-present)\u00a0behind a strong six inning, two earned-run start from\nCal Rutherford\n.\nRutherford (Canton, Mich./Detroit Catholic Central)\n(1-0) struck out a career-best eight batters and earned his first win of the season while Akron's Trieg Matthews (2-1) was tagged with the loss.\nAfter falling behind 2-0, Eastern scored a total of six unanswered runs, plating two runs in the fourth, fifth, and seventh innings for the 6-2 win.\nHow it Happened\nAkron struck first in the top of the third inning, taking a 2-0 lead on a two-run double.\nEastern Michigan found its rhythm in the bottom of the fourth, pulling even when\nDemir Heidelberg\n(Homewood, Ill./Homewood Flossmor)\nlaced a double down the left field line, driving in\nKeegan Knupp\n(Lewis Center, Ohio/Olentangy Orange)\nand\nKevin Krill\n(White Lake, Mich./Oakland/Kalamazoo Valley C.C.)\n.\nThe Eagles seized control in the fifth as Knupp came through with a clutch two-run single to right center, plating\nDevan Zirwas\n(Imperial, Pa./West Allegheny/VCU)\nand\nKriss Sydlowski\n(Ann Arbor, Mich./Saline/ USC Sumpter)\nfor a 4-2 advantage. The momentum continued in the seventh when\nNick Weaver\n(Streamwood, Ill./Streamwood/Elgin C.C.)\ndelivered a two-RBI single, bringing home Knupp and\nDrew Jones\n(Cleveland, Ohio/Brush/Ohio State)\nto cap the scoring.\nLandon Mueller\n(Fremont, Neb./Fremont/Omaha)\nretired the side in order in the top of the ninth to secure the series win for EMU with a 6-2 Sunday final.\nGame Notes\n\u00bb Eastern's record improved to 6-17 (2-7 MAC), and Akron's fell to 10-12 (4-5 MAC).\n\u00bb Eastern out-hit its opponent for the sixth time this season with nine hits to Akron's four. It moved to 3-3 when outhitting opponents as it has accomplished the feat in each of the last two games.\n\u00bb Eastern has posted nine or more hits in seven of its last nine contests.\n\u00bb\u00a0The game marked the first series win and MAC series victory of the 2026 campaign. The game also marked the Eagles' first time winning on a Sunday this season.\n\u00bb\nCal Rutherford\ngot the ball for his second consecutive start. He went 6.0 innings, allowing two runs off four\u00a0hits while striking out a career-best eight batters and issuing one walk. His eight strikeouts tie for the most by an Eagle this season after\nJohn Carmichael\n(Destrehan, La./Destrehan/McCLennan C.C.)\nsat down eight via the strikeout at Austin Peay, Feb. 20. Rutherford and Carmichael's eight strikeouts rank third in the MAC single-game standings.\n\u00bb\nKeegan Knupp\nwent 2-for-4 at the dish with two RBI. The game marked his second with multiple hits and RBI as he previously did so at Austin Peay, Feb. 21 (three hits), and at SIUE, March 1 (two RBI).\n\u00bb\nDemir Heidelberg\ndrove in a pair of runs for the first time in his career with a two-run double down the left-field line in the fourth inning. The double marked his fourth extra-base hit of the season as he has recorded one double in his last three games.\n\u00bb\nNick Weaver\ndrove in two runs, marking his second game with two or more RBI this season. Weaver first drove in multiple runs with a career-best three RBI at Ball State, March 15.\n\u00bb\nDevan Zirwas\nrecorded two hits for his sixth multi-hit game of the season, the second most on the team. He recorded his sixth double of the season in the eighth, marking his team-best 16th extra-base hit.\nHistorical Notes\n\u00bb Eastern met Akron for the 80th time. Eastern holds a 50-30 record all-time against the Zips and a 12-14 mark when facing it at Oestrike Stadium since 1999.\n\u00bb Eastern won a series for the first time under Interim Head Coach\nTrevor Beerman\n. The series win marked the first MAC series victory for the first-year skipper as well.\nUp Next\nThe Eagles will face Youngstown State University Tuesday, March 24, at 3 p.m., at Oestrike Stadium in Ypsilanti, Mich.\nFollow Us\nKeep up with all things Eastern baseball by following the team on X @EMU_Baseball, and on Instagram @emu_baseball.",
    "watch_url": null
  },
